efs.html#Asymptotics.IsBigO\">=O[</a><span class=\"fn\">l</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsBigO\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsBigOWith\">IsBigOWith</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">l</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Definition of `IsBigO` in terms of `IsBigOWith`. We record it in a lemma as `IsBigO` is\nirreducible. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.isBigO_iff_isBigOWith","kind":"theorem","line":107,"name":"Asymptotics.isBigO_iff_isBigOWith","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.lean#L107-L109"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.«term_=O[_]_»\"><span class=\"name\">Asymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_=O[_]_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The Landau notation `f =O[l] g` where `f` and `g` are two functions on a type `α` and `l` is\na filter on `α`, means that eventually for `l`, `‖f‖` is bounded by a constant multiple of `‖g‖`.\nIn other words, `‖f‖ / ‖g‖` is eventually bounded, modulo division by zero issues that are avoided\nby this definition. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.«term_=O[_]_»","kind":"def","line":104,"name":"Asymptotics.«term_=O[_]_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd